<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1120719-just-finished-the-book-it-was-amazing-a">Just finished the book. It was amazing. A lot of the women were referred to as &quot;liaisons&quot;. It was attached to many different military roles. What is this referring to? I think of a liaison as a go between. Were they possibly a runner or messenger?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1120719'><a id="like_count_community_question_1120719" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/1120719?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">3 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F4025275-war-s-unwomanly-face">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
